    "comment": "Rationale: Fig9AB shows EFA6C localization in dendrites of Purkinje cells and spines by light microscopy, Fig9D shows postsynaptic localization by immuno-EM, which is verified by subcellular fractionation where EFA6C shows enrichment in the PSD95 fraction (Fig8B).\n\n24/10/2017 Pim\n- The authors mention \"showing strong immunoreactivity in the dendritic spines (sp) having the post-synaptic density (arrows)\". The immuno-EM picture is rather vague but staining seems to be more widespread than the PSD itself.. Experimental description: Figure legends \"adult mouse cerebellum \"",
